  "texts": [
    "The second (b) has characteristics that suggest a tectonic teleseism (Teleseism I, main text); however it is possible that other modes of brittle deformation are contributing to the signal (investigated further in Fig.",
    "S4 in the Supplement).",
    "The third (c) also has characteristics that suggest a tectonic teleseism (Teleseism II, main text).",
    "Top row (purple overlay): detection by multi-STA/LTA, with recommended parameters (i.e., sta = 0.03, lta = 100, sta = 18, lta = 56, and = 10).",
    "Second row (light-orange overlay): detection by the recursive algorithm with RECmin parameters (i.e., the minimum sta-lta pairs sampled by the multi-STA/LTA with recommended parameters: sta = 0.03 and lta = 100)."
